Genesis Global Capital, the lending business of Genesis Trading, last week <a href="https://www.theblock.co/post/187545/genesis-global-capital-suspends-redemptions-with-impact-spreading-to-gemini" data-v-f87c67ca="">temporarily suspended redemptions</a> and new loan originations in the wake of FTX's collapse and the earlier Three Arrows Capital implosion. At the time, parent company Digital Currency Group said business operations at DCG and its other wholly owned subsidiaries were not affected.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
DCG gave Genesis Trading a $140 million equity infusion after it said its derivatives business had $175 million locked up on the FTX platform.&nbsp;
